reviewText: Chiefly interesting because of the performance of Xavier Dolan, actor-director, because I had never heard him act in English before or seen him perform under the direction of someone else.  The film might have been much more interesting had he reworked the script and directed it, but, obviously, it was useful to him to get in some screen exposure in English which he speaks with no particular accent and in which he is perfectly fluent.

Not what I was expecting... There really was no point to this movie. I kept waiting for something to happen, but it didn't. I read the reviews on this, that's why I watched it... By the reviews are dead wrong!!
The movie that was advertised was not the movie that played.
A microcosm in several angles of the pain of life.
I loved this movie. The actors performances were phenomenal. The movie holds its mystery until the very end.
